{"questionId":"10032","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Matrices <strong><em>A</em></strong>, <strong><em>B</em></strong> and <strong><em>C</em></strong> are defined by</p>\n<p><strong><em>A&nbsp;</em></strong>=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  5&amp;1 \\\\   7&amp;2  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>B</em></strong>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  2&amp;4 \\\\   { - 3}&amp;{15}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>15</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>C</em></strong>&nbsp;= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  9&amp;{ - 7} \\\\   8&amp;2  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>9</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>7</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Let <strong><em>X</em></strong> be an unknown 2 × 2 matrix satisfying the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><em>AX</em> </strong>+<strong> <em>B</em> </strong>=<strong> <em>C</em></strong>.</p>\n<p>This equation may be solved for <strong><em>X</em></strong> by rewriting it in the form</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><em>X</em> </strong>=<strong> <em>A</em></strong><sup>−1</sup><strong>&nbsp;<em>D</em></strong>.</p>\n<p>where <strong><em>D</em></strong> is a 2 × 2 matrix.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <strong><em>D</em></strong>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>AX</em></strong> = <strong><em>C</em></strong>&nbsp;− <strong><em>B</em></strong>&nbsp;(may be implied)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><em>X</em></strong> = <strong><em>A</em></strong><sup>−1 </sup><strong>(<em>C</em></strong><em>−</em><strong><em>B</em>)</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><em>D</em> </strong>=<strong> <em>C </em></strong><em>−</em><strong>&nbsp;<em>B</em></strong> &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  7&amp;{ - 11} \\\\   {11}&amp;{ - 13}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>13</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)&nbsp; (N3)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10032","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.6b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find D.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}